subSubSection.paragraph:
Colouration (Figs 15c, 16
e-f
): Fronto-orbital plate, parafacial and upper occiput blackish-brown; frontal vitta brown; lower occiput, postgena, gena, genal groove, facial ridge, and face yellowish-red in ground colour. Head covered with grey microtomentum, denser on parafacial than fronto-orbital plate. Antenna yellow. Palpus yellow. Thorax mostly brown especially on scutum, largely reddish-yellow on pleura. Legs mostly brownish-yellow. Basicosta yellow. Wing membrane hyaline, veins yellowish. Abdomen yellowish-red ventrally, laterally and dorsolaterally, shading into brown dorsomedially. Syntergite 1+2 microtomentose only on mid-dorsal depression; tergites 3-5 with a narrow basal band of whitish-grey reflecting microtomentum, which is medially expanded into a triangular prolongation almost reaching posterior margins of tergites (Fig. 16f).
